EmailTemplate.name: IBCS Transition
EmailTemplate.subject: Ref nr {!Case.CaseNumber} - {!Case.Subject}
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear Sir, Madam,
As you have been informed a few months ago, the IBCS program will be ending on December 31st, 2014.
The former IBCS Consolidators may continue to offer their services for any interested Airlines, either through their standard GSA contract or any other agreement for provision of services. The IBCS Consolidators have recently notified IATA on the airlines willing to continue using their services (such as local representation, use of the Local VAT, etc..). As part of such notification, we have been informed that your airline either has not provided feedback or does not wish to use anymore the services of the former IBCS Consolidators in the following countries:
1. Standard Countries (Countries for which local representation and/or local VAT is not mandatory)
List…….
2. Non Standard Countries (Countries for which local representation and/or local VAT is mandatory, and/or where special requirements exist)
List……
Action Required from your side:
Please note that the submission of the attached Transition Form to ensure compliance of your airline in the above designated operation (points 1a and 1b) is required. Moreover, an Additional Requirements Form is required for the below list of countries:
o List……
Your settlement instructions should be updated for the operation(s) mentioned below:
List........
You may submit a Local Bank Mandate (template attached). The bank mandate must be issued from your Company’s Head Office and signed by two Head Office senior officers, at least one of which must be:
• Chief Financial Officer (CFO) or
• Head of Treasury or Cash Management Department
OR
As an alternative, your airline may apply for ICCS in these designated operation(s) (if available). In such case, please contact ICCS department (iccso@iata.org) as soon as possible so the necessary actions are done within the timeline.
The Dead line to receive the documents for NON-standard countries is 15/01/2015 The Dead line to receive the documents for standard countries is 29/01/2015
Notes:
1. The Transition form and Additional Requirements Form are attached to this email.
2. Submission of the Transition Form and Additional Requirements Form (if applicable) in scanned format is acceptable subject to receive the originals afterwards within the above mentioned time lines. Please submit the scanned copies by replying directly to this email.
3. You will find on the Resource Center of our IATA Customer Services Portal: www.iata.org/cs the country requirements specific for each country. You can select the applicable country and the line of business (BSP - Passenger Airline) from the drop-down menus. Please click Here to access directly the IATA Resource Center.
4. The submission of the documents is required to ensure that:
a. the BSPLink Master Table (containing information such as Airline address and VAT that appear in the billing analysis and other reports) is kept accurate
b. the BSPlink access details is sent to the new person in charge to handle BSPlink-related matters (example: Maintenance of Ticketing Authority, issuance of ADM/ACM, Refund Application maintenance, etc…)
5. if the documents are not received on time, your participation records and presence in the specific BSP Operation may not be updated anymore leading to non-compliance with country's requirements.
6. The processing of transactions (such as ticketing issuance) will not be disrupted after December 31st, 2014. However the submission of the documents requested in the current email by the established dead line is mandatory.
7. Your Airline may decide to keep using certain services of the former Consolidator next year, e.g. either as GSA or Legal Representative of your Airline. Such services may include local representation, use of the GSA’s Local VAT (if permitted), etc. The relationship and any corresponding agreement is solely between the airline and this entity.
8. Your airline can appoint any GSA or Legal Representative available in a country at any stage (within the timeline set or at any later stage) and as long as it is communicated to IATA through the Customer Portal: www.iata.org/cs
for
Your airline may decide to Voluntary Withdrawal from a specific BSP operation, in which case, please note that a 3 months notice is applicable. During that timeline, your airline is required to keep using the services of the former IBCS Consolidator until the effective end date of the designated operation. To notify IATA, please fill in the attached Voluntary Withdrawal form and submit it to us.
9. Your airline can notify of a new address or new VAT to be used in a specific market through the Customer Portal: www.iata.org/cs
Please send the original document to the below address: ATTN: Global Airline Participation Team - IBCS transition International Air Transport Association (IATA) 33 Route de l'Aeroport 1215 Geneva Switzerland
Once the document is received, we will notify you accordingly.
Kind Regards,
{!Case.OwnerFullName},
Global Airline Participation Team
Financial and Distribution Services
International Air Transport Association
33, Route de l'Aéroport
1215 Geneva 15 Airport
Switzerland
